{"title_page": "Alain Pichon", "text_new": "{{about||the French para table tennis player|Alain Pichon (table tennis)|the French anthropologist|Alain le Pichon}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Alain Pichon\n| image       = AlainPichon2013.jpg\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1966|4|19}}<ref>https://www.facebook.com/alainpichonhair/info</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Nantes]], [[France]]\n| residence = [[London, UK]] \n| known_for   = [[Hair (TV series)|Hair TV Series]]\n| occupation  = Celebrity Fashion Hairstylist, Television Personality\n| website = http://alainpichon.com\n}}\n\n'''Alain Pichon''' (born 19 April 1966) is a French hairstylist, and television personality.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/alainpichonhair/info |title=Alain Pichon Hair |publisher=Alain Pichon |date= |accessdate=2014-11-03}}</ref>  His participation as a judge on the [[Hair (TV series)|Hair TV Series]] made him a British household name in 2014. The first series was broadcast in early 2014 on [[BBC Three]], and achieved the highest viewing figures for the TV channel.<ref>https://www.theguardian.com/media/2014/mar/05/hair-viewers-bbc3-eastenders-family-guy</ref><ref>http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p01nq2rh</ref> The show aired in Australia on the [[ABC2]] channel later in 2014.<ref>http://www.abc.net.au/tv/programs/hair/</ref> A second series is confirmed on [[BBC Two]] in 2015.<ref>http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/news/a606821/hair-steve-jones-competition-moves-to-bbc-two-for-series-2.html</ref> He is well known as the hairdresser to the worldwide celebrity [[David Beckham]] amongst many others.<ref>http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2014-02-19/david-beckhams-best-and-worst-hairstyles-by-the-man-who-created-them</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nAs a fourth-generation hairdresser, international session stylist Alain Pichon's passion for hair runs in his blood.\nHe first started training in his local French salon, which had links to the [[Vidal Sassoon]] Academy. By the age of 23, Alain was in London working for [[Toni & Guy]] where he soon became Artistic Director and travelled the world educating at shows and seminars.\n\nAlain started his freelance career as a hairstylist at 28, working together with designers' collections on fashion shows, with renowned photographers on well-known magazines and as a consultant for international product companies and feature films.<ref>http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/profiles/3nyy0hslCfLSZbz5kSc2tPf/alain-pichon</ref><ref>http://www.hungertv.com/beauty/feature/s-magazine-alain-pichon/</ref><ref>http://alainpichon.com/profile.html</ref>\n\nAlain is represented by the global management agency, CLM <ref>http://www.clm-agency.com/hair-make-up/hair/alain-pichon/</ref>\n\n== Clientele ==\n\nHe has collaborated on advertising campaigns, such as [[Prada]], [[Calvin Klein]], [[Dior]], [[Yves Saint Laurent (designer)|YSL]], [[Donna Karan]], [[Hugo Boss]] and for many catwalk shows in New York, Paris, London and Milan.<ref>http://www.vogue.it/en/beauty/beauty-news/2010/05/alain-pichon</ref>\n\nOver the years Alain has worked with [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]], [[Claudia Schiffer]], [[Kylie Minogue]], [[Sienna Miller]], [[Britney Spears]], [[Scarlett Johansson]], [[Trudie Styler]], [[Prince William]] and [[Prince Harry]].<ref>http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/profiles/3nyy0hslCfLSZbz5kSc2tPf/alain-pichon</ref><ref>http://www.nowmagazine.co.uk/celebrity-hair/538284/david-beckham-borrows-prince-harry-s-hair-stylist</ref>\n\n== Editorial ==\n\nAlain works with many of the world's top magazines, including several editions of [[Vogue Magazine]], [[Another Magazine]], [[W Magazine]], [[Num\u00e9ro]], [[Dazed & Confused (magazine)]].<ref>http://www.vogue.it/en/beauty/beauty-news/2010/05/alain-pichon</ref>\n\n== Television ==\nIn 2014 Pichon had his TV debut as a judge on the [[BBC Three]] [[Hair (TV series)|Hair TV Series]], alongside [[Denise McAdam]] and [[Steve Jones (Welsh presenter)|Steve Jones (presenter)]].\nThe show netted 785,000 viewers on [[BBC Three]] and was most watched show on the channel, followed by [[EastEnders]] and [[Family Guy]].<ref>https://www.theguardian.com/media/2014/mar/05/hair-viewers-bbc3-eastenders-family-guy</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nGrowing up in France with three older sisters, Alain was surrounded with passion for fashion, magazines and beauty. His father, his grandfather and his great grandfather before him were barbers so it seemed only natural to Alain to follow in the family tradition.\n\nAlain has been married to Eva Charlotta since 1993. They have 3 children, Carmen Adora 21, Viktor 15 and Alfons 5<ref>http://www.timeandleisure.co.uk/articles/food/3072-review-al-forno.html</ref><ref>http://www.boots.com/en/Our-Biggest-Ever-Beauty-Event/Top-10-hair-repair/Meet-Alain-Pichton/</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n<!-- Per [[WP:ELMINOFFICIAL]], choose one official website only -->\n* {{official website|http://www.alainpichon.com}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pichon, Alain}}\n[[Category:1966 births]]\n[[Category:French expatriates in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:French hairdressers]]\n[[Category:Television personalities from London]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Nantes]]\n", "text_old": "{{about||the French para table tennis player|Alain Pichon (table tennis)|the French anthropologist|Alain le Pichon}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Alain Pichon\n| image       = AlainPichon2013.jpg\n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1966|4|19}}<ref>https://www.facebook.com/alainpichonhair/info</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Nantes]], [[France]]\n| residence = [[London, UK]] \n| known_for   = [[Hair (TV series)|Hair TV Series]]\n| occupation  = Celebrity Fashion Hairstylist, Television Personality\n| website = http://alainpichon.com\n}}\n\n'''Alain Pichon''' (born 19 April 1966) is a French hairstylist, and television personality.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/alainpichonhair/info |title=Alain Pichon Ha